<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 7:56PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Scattered strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Madison
and Beaverhead Counties through 845 PM MDT...
At 754 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
about 10 miles southwest of Twin Bridges moving northeast at 25 mph.
Other scattered thunderstorms were located across northern
Beaverhead and southern Madison counties.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Beaverhead and Madison counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
